The paper focuses on autonomous navigation, which is a core topic in robotics, and proposes a new framework for navigation based on GPS-level localization. Therefore, cs.RO (Robotics) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also uses deep learning techniques to handle raw sensory data, which involves computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The proposed method also uses a conditional adversarial network, which is a popular technique in deep learning and falls under the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper deals with navigation in real-world environments, which involves system integration and control (cs.SY).
